We came home.

96
00:04:11,441 --> 00:04:15,477
Found things not quite
as hospitable as we'd hoped.

97
00:04:15,479 --> 00:04:17,812
No infrastructure...

98
00:04:17,814 --> 00:04:21,065
No government, no orders.

99
00:04:21,067 --> 00:04:22,283
So we went to the White House,

100
00:04:22,285 --> 00:04:23,651
and we were able to get our hands

101
00:04:23,653 --> 00:04:25,320
on many of the Presidential
files and directives.

102
00:04:25,322 --> 00:04:27,489
This is the secretary of the Navy.

103
00:04:27,491 --> 00:04:30,492
I understand you...
You knew him pretty well.

104
00:04:30,494 --> 00:04:34,913
<i>The U.S. Navy is currently on
a mission to find the materials</i>

105
00:04:34,915 --> 00:04:37,832
<i>for a vaccine to combat the pandemic.</i>

106
00:04:37,834 --> 00:04:39,501
<i>If you're viewing this video,</i>

107
00:04:39,503 --> 00:04:42,387
<i>you are part of the new network
of facilities</i>

108
00:04:42,389 --> 00:04:45,390
<i>in the United States
and certain foreign countries,</i>

109
00:04:45,392 --> 00:04:49,644
<i>which were chosen to produce
and distribute the vaccine.</i>

110
00:04:49,646 --> 00:04:53,431
<i>You'll be able to communicate
with the civilian command</i>

111
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:54,682
<i>with each other.</i>

112
00:04:54,684 --> 00:04:57,769
<i>Hopefully, you'll then start producing</i>

113
00:04:57,771 --> 00:04:59,604
<i>and distributing the vaccine,</i>

114
00:04:59,606 --> 00:05:04,108
<i>and we can get to the task
of rebuilding our great nation.</i>

115
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:05,527
<i>Godspeed.</i>

116
00:05:05,529 --> 00:05:08,196
[Click]

117
00:05:08,198 --> 00:05:09,747
We have the cure, sir.

118
00:05:10,584 --> 00:05:14,118
Dr. Scott was able to produce it
right here on this ship.

119
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:17,705
Guess you wouldn't have
any need for it yourself.

120
00:05:17,707 --> 00:05:19,207
The rest of the world,

121
00:05:19,209 --> 00:05:23,511
the ones who aren't lucky enough
to be naturally immune...

122
00:05:25,098 --> 00:05:27,348
We got to Norfolk, we found pilots,

123
00:05:27,350 --> 00:05:30,101
we sent doses around the country
and to Europe,

124
00:05:30,103 --> 00:05:31,553
as we were ordered to do.

125
00:05:31,555 --> 00:05:35,056
The project to mass-produce
the cure was well under way,

126
00:05:35,058 --> 00:05:37,525
and then we ran into some problems.

127
00:05:39,062 --> 00:05:42,397
This is a recording made
by one of our scientists.

128
00:05:42,399 --> 00:05:44,566
He was trying to get a message
through to Dr. Scott.

129
00:05:49,489 --> 00:05:51,072
<i>Rachel.</i>

130
00:05:51,074 --> 00:05:53,458
<i>Oh, God, I pray this gets to you.</i>

131
00:05:53,460 --> 00:05:55,877
<i>Listen, w-w-we're under attack, Rachel.</i>

132
00:05:55,879 --> 00:05:57,412
<i>But it's important...</i>

133
00:05:57,414 --> 00:05:59,747
<i>It's important that you learn this.</i>

134
00:05:59,749 --> 00:06:02,166
<i>I've been working with the data
you sent me about the cure,</i>

135
00:06:02,168 --> 00:06:03,751
<i>and I think I've found a way to help.</i>

136
00:06:03,753 --> 00:06:04,886
[<i>Gunfire</i>]

137
00:06:04,888 --> 00:06:06,421
<i>I'm sending you the data now.</i>

138
00:06:06,423 --> 00:06:08,473
- [<i>Gunfire continues</i>]
<i>- I didn't... oh, God.</i>

139
00:06:08,475 --> 00:06:09,340
<i>Oh, God.</i>

140
00:06:09,342 --> 00:06:11,309
<i>Listen, it's all worked out.</i>

141
00:06:11,311 --> 00:06:13,094
<i>All you have to do is...</i>

142
00:06:13,096 --> 00:06:15,146
<i>I just somehow pray that this
file gets to you, Rachel...</i>

143
00:06:15,148 --> 00:06:17,649
[<i>man speaking indistinctly</i>]

144
00:06:17,651 --> 00:06:20,151
[<i>Crash</i>]

145
00:06:20,153 --> 00:06:22,487
MacDowell: <i>Come on, now. Take it all!</i>

146
00:06:22,489 --> 00:06:24,405
<i>We need to find that server.</i>

147
00:06:24,407 --> 00:06:27,075
<i>Okay, Doc. Stand up.</i>

148
00:06:27,077 --> 00:06:28,076
<i>No, please. Please.</i>

149
00:06:28,078 --> 00:06:30,445
[<i>Two gunshots</i>]

150
00:06:35,785 --> 00:06:38,870
<i>You might recognize that Irish accent.</i>

151
00:06:38,872 --> 00:06:41,205
Those were Sean Ramsey's people.

152
00:06:43,126 --> 00:06:46,010
<i>They gained access to our secret network,</i>

153
00:06:46,012 --> 00:06:47,595
the location of all our labs,

154
00:06:47,597 --> 00:06:49,681
and they blew them up
with their long-range missiles.

155
00:06:49,683 --> 00:06:51,349
Destroyed our limited infrastructure,

156
00:06:51,351 --> 00:06:53,434
murdered our scientists...
All because they believe

157
00:06:53,436 --> 00:06:55,687
that they are the inheritors of the earth.

158
00:06:58,775 --> 00:07:01,976
That's why Captain Chandler
rescued you from the Ramseys.

159
00:07:03,863 --> 00:07:06,864
<i>I can only assume
you knew nothing about this.</i>

160
00:07:06,866 --> 00:07:09,367
I mean, if you did...

161
00:07:15,325 --> 00:07:17,325
<i>This is a comprehensive look
at Dr. Scott's protocols,</i>

162
00:07:17,327 --> 00:07:19,410
experiments, and trials.

163
00:07:22,549 --> 00:07:24,966
Complete Captain's logs,
combat center records,

164
00:07:24,968 --> 00:07:26,417
including our attempt at a response

165
00:07:26,419 --> 00:07:28,219
to the Ramseys' assault on our labs.

166
00:07:28,221 --> 00:07:30,171
It's not easy to listen to,

167
00:07:30,173 --> 00:07:33,057
but I think it'll be informative.

168
00:07:37,564 --> 00:07:40,398
<i>I'll let the Captain know
that you've been briefed.</i>

169
00:07:41,017 --> 00:07:42,266
[<i>Door opens</i>]

170
00:07:42,268 --> 00:07:43,768
Leaving him without a guard?

171
00:07:43,770 --> 00:07:46,154
We need to see what he does
when he's alone.

172
00:08:02,756 --> 00:08:04,756
- Hey.
- Well done, Detective.

173
00:08:04,758 --> 00:08:07,458
What's he doing?

174
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:11,045
Pacing, biting his fingernails.

175
00:08:11,047 --> 00:08:13,264
He's eyeing the laptop.

176
00:08:13,266 --> 00:08:16,267
Got to be curious
after what I just dumped on him.

177
00:08:16,269 --> 00:08:17,602
Here he goes.

178
00:08:30,233 --> 00:08:31,733
What the hell is he...

179
00:08:33,570 --> 00:08:35,236
What is that?

180
00:08:38,124 --> 00:08:39,741
Nobody frisked him?

181
00:08:39,743 --> 00:08:40,792
He was unarmed.

182
00:08:40,794 --> 00:08:42,243
Can we get a better look at the monitor?

183
00:08:42,245 --> 00:08:43,661
Alisha: I'll change angles, sir.

184
00:08:52,839 --> 00:08:54,338
Can you zoom?

185
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:57,341
Sean: <i>It isn't a question
of what we've lost,</i>

186
00:08:57,343 --> 00:09:00,311
<i>it's a question of what we've been given...</i>

187
00:09:00,313 --> 00:09:01,763
That's Ramsey.

188
00:09:01,765 --> 00:09:05,817
<i>And that is a chance...
A chance to start again.</i>

189
00:09:05,819 --> 00:09:09,353
<i>A chance to renew the human
spirit with our valiance,</i>

190
00:09:09,355 --> 00:09:12,240
<i>a chance to reclaim the world.</i>

191
00:09:12,242 --> 00:09:15,693
<i>This is our calling,</i>

192
00:09:15,695 --> 00:09:23,117
<i>and if you are watching this,
know that we are calling you.</i>

193
00:09:26,289 --> 00:09:27,872
[Exhales deeply]

194
00:09:33,045 --> 00:09:36,245
Sean: <i>And you must prepare yourself
for the task ahead.</i>

195
00:09:36,247 --> 00:09:37,613
<i>There will be doubters...</i>

196
00:09:37,615 --> 00:09:39,448
We have to figure out
what else is on that drive.

197
00:09:39,450 --> 00:09:41,216
We walk in there and ask him for it,

198
00:09:41,218 --> 00:09:42,818
he'll know we've been surveilling him.

199
00:09:42,820 --> 00:09:44,169
He'll clam up completely.

200
00:09:44,171 --> 00:09:46,338
When you're trying to break
an Al-Qaeda operative,

201
00:09:46,340 --> 00:09:49,041
you don't let him keep messages
from Bin Laden in his pocket.

202
00:09:49,043 --> 00:09:50,342
We take away the computer.

203
00:09:50,344 --> 00:09:52,211
We prevent him from accessing the messages.

204
00:09:52,213 --> 00:09:54,463
Look at that man. He's a lost cause.

205
00:09:54,465 --> 00:09:56,131
We don't know that, sir... Not yet.

206
00:09:56,133 --> 00:09:57,883
Right, and while we're trying
to figure that out,

207
00:09:57,885 --> 00:10:00,602
we're sitting here burning fuel,
hiding behind this island,

208
00:10:00,604 --> 00:10:03,022
wondering what the sub is up to,
what its plans are.

209
00:10:03,024 --> 00:10:04,556
We have to find out how they communicate.

210
00:10:04,558 --> 00:10:07,476
We have to find out
how Ramsey sent those messages

211
00:10:07,478 --> 00:10:09,395
across the country all the way from Europe.

212
00:10:10,364 --> 00:10:12,981
I appreciate what you're trying to do, sir,

213
00:10:12,983 --> 00:10:14,983
but getting intel out of this man

214
00:10:14,985 --> 00:10:17,319
has to be priority number one.

215
00:10:19,990 --> 00:10:21,707
<i>But you, Jeffrey,</i>

216
00:10:21,709 --> 00:10:24,126
<i>you were put on the earth for this,</i>

217
00:10:24,128 --> 00:10:26,328
- [door opens]
- <i>To fight the forces of...</i>

218
00:10:26,330 --> 00:10:27,496
[beep]

